{"questionId":"14156","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Let&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( x \\right) = 2\\,{\\text{sin}}\\left( {3x} \\right) + 4\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>sin</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n</math></span> for&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x \\in \\mathbb{R}\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Let&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"g\\left( x \\right) = 5f\\left( {2x} \\right)\">\n  <mi>g</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>5</mn>\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The function <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"g\">\n  <mi>g</mi>\n</math></span> can be written in the form <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"g\\left( x \\right) = 10\\,{\\text{sin}}\\left( {bx} \\right) + c\">\n  <mi>g</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>10</mn>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>sin</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>b</mi>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>The equation&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"g\\left( x \\right) = 12\">\n  <mi>g</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>12</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;has two solutions where&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\pi \">\n  <mi>π</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;≤&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;≤&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\frac{{4\\pi }}{3}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>4</mn>\n        <mi>π</mi>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </mfrac>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.&nbsp;Find both solutions.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>valid approach &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg&nbsp;</em>&nbsp;&nbsp;<img src=\"__IMG__/74a480184cf34729e293802a39b0c481946b103f.png\">,&nbsp; <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{si}}{{\\text{n}}^{ - 1}}\\left( { - \\frac{8}{{10}}} \\right){\\text{,&nbsp; }}6x =&nbsp; - 0.927{\\text{,&nbsp; }} - 0.154549{\\text{,&nbsp; &nbsp;}}x = 0.678147\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>si</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>n</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>8</mn>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>10</mn>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,&nbsp;</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mn>6</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>0.927</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,&nbsp;</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>0.154549</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,&nbsp;</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0.678147</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>M1</strong></em> for any correct value for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> or <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"6x\">\n  <mn>6</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> which lies outside the domain of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p>3.81974,&nbsp; 4.03424</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = 3.82\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>3.82</mn>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = 4.03\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>4.03</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;(do not accept answers in degrees)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1 N3</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14156","referenceCode":"19M.2.SL.TZ1.S_8d","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"The equation g ( x ) = 12 has two solutions where π ≤ x ≤ 4 π 3 . Find both solutions.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.7—Circular functions: graphs, composites, transformations","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.8—Solving trig equations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}